doc.after: The J79 is a single spool turbojet with a seventeen stage compressor with a novel arrangement of variable stator blades which allow the engine to develop pressure similar to a twin spool engine at a much lower weight Each blade is made largely of stainless steel Each blade today costs several thousand dollars to replace The compressor blades are mounted on disks the first seven stages being made of titanium and spaced with corrosion resistant not stainless steel spacers 5
